To convert markdown formatted text to HTML, we can use the following C++ function. This function uses the `markdown` library, which is a simple markdown parser written in C++. You can find the complete code for the `markdown` library in the given link:

[markdown-library]: https://github.com/mojotech/markdown

Here's the C++ function that takes a reference to a std::string containing markdown formatted text and returns a std::string containing HTML formatted text:

```cpp
#include "markdown.hpp"

std::string markdown_to_html(const std::string& markdown_text) {
    markdown::Options options;
    options.convert_urls = true;
    options.convert_emails = true;
    options.convert_links = true;

    std::string html_text;
    markdown::markdown(markdown_text, html_text, options);
    return html_text;
}
```

You can use this function like this:

```cpp
std::string markdown_text = "This is a markdown text.\n\nThis is a heading.\n";
std::string html_text = markdown_to_html(markdown_text);

std::cout << html_text << std::endl;
```

Please note that you need to include the `markdown.hpp` header file from the `markdown` library in your C++ project to use the `markdown_to_html` function. You can do this by adding the following line to your include files:

```cpp
#include "markdown.hpp"
```

Also, make sure to link the `libmarkdown` library when compiling your project. The `markdown` library provides a static library for C++, so you can link it using the following command:

```cpp
g++ your_program.cpp -lmarkdown
```

Replace `your_program.cpp` with the name of your C++ source file.
